<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p>Trains run regularly between Walsall and Birmingham New Street station.</p><br/><p>To walk to the hospital, turn left out of Walsall station, walk towards the 'T' junction, turn right into Bridgeman Street. The walk is slightly uphill and takes about 10 minutes. Continue over the traffic lights, a pedestrian entrance to the hospital is 50 metres on the leftt</p><br/><p>M6 Junction 7 follow signs to Walsall along the Birmingham Road picking up the Ring Road by turning left at the Boundary Hotel island. Turn right at the junction signed 'Walsall Manor Hospital'and on to Bescot Rd, straight on is Pleck Rd</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>The Trust operates a 'pay on foot' system for car parking, the charge is £2 for the first hour and £1 per hour after the first hour up to a maximum daily fee of £6<br/><br/>Weekly concessionary passes are available for regular visitors to the hospital at a charge of £13 per week.</p>
